description:
A vague humanoid apparition appears to Mr. Alec Kyle, an employee of E-Branch, and begins telling a story...

We are introduced to Harry Keogh, a strange boy who is picked on by his schoolmates, and Dragosani, a KGB operative who is able to pull information from a dead body while ripping it to shreds.
This is a continuation of the story, Necroscope, started in issue 1.
The story continues from issue 2, starting in issue 1.
The story continues.

The story, starting in issue 1, concludes.

This ends the comic version of The Necroscope, by Brian Lumley, first in a series of novels.

name: Barres à Mines et Coyotes Roses

description: Stalked by a laser-wielding shark and ravaged by a rogue wave, the islanders are washed up on the shore of a strange landmass, only to discover that when they die, they die for good. Now without their self-appointed leader, Ooga must step up to take control of the group, but will his intervention be enough to save the tribe?
name: The Gem of Life Part 2

description: With the tribe's numbers dwindling faster than their coconut supply, Ooga leads the remaining survivors towards the temple where their powers are said to originate, but with a hungry tyrannosaurus rex in hot pursuit, can they outrun the prehistoric lizard and make amends with their gods before it's too late?
name: The Gem of Life Part 3

description: With the tribe's mortality hanging in the balance, Ooga must travel deep into the temple to confront the unmerciful gods, but with the rest of the pygmies turned into zombies, can the unlikely hero complete the mission on his own or is the tribe destined to be disbanded for good?
name: The Gem of Life Part 4

description: In the first hit comic book series based on the best-selling iPhone app, unlikely hero Ooga questioned the meaning of life, now in this ALL NEW holiday one-shot, the tribe of pygmies begin to question if they're alone in the world after Nooby is kidnapped from the island and taken to an odd workshop built out of ice where a mysterious and lonely man, jolly as he is, tries to clone Nooby and start a family. Also featuring everyone's favorite ice monster! ROAR!
name: X-Mas Marks the Spot

description: BECAUSE YOU DEMANDED IT! Pocket God the comic RETURNS with a brand new story arc- "Tale of Two Pygmies"! In this issue, we kick off a 3 part story arc that will redefine the Pygmy world and set the stage for the introduction of, wait for it, NEW CHARACTERS! But before we do all that, there is a Squid-Ball game to play!
name: Tale of Two Pygmies Part 1 (of 3)

description: "Tale of Two Pygmies" Part 2! In this issue, things come to a head between Ooga and Klik and the rest of the tribe is forced to choose sides. Will the tribe stay together? What is the new mystery surrounding the Gem of Life and why is it causing so much trouble in the tribe?! Plus, Nooby gets... Dodo Bumps!?
name: Tale of Two Pygmies Part 2 (of 3)

description: This is the final chapter of the Tale of Two Pygmies storyline and it is jam-packed with goodies! The tribe is split and things are taking a turn for the worse! The mystery of who took the Gem of Life is revealed and the repercussions of who it is will change the Pygmy world forever! Not enough? How about the ominous return of NEWBIE!
name: Tale of Two Pygmies Part 3 (of 3)

description: Infestation has arrived in Pocket God!
name: Infestation Part 1 of 1

description: Sun and the boys head out on the seas of adventure! But what discoverys wash ashore? All this and the return of an old friend!
name: A Quest Called Tribe Part 1 (of 4)

description: Issue 11 is here! Part two of the 'A QUEST CALLED TRIBE' story arc! Sun, the mysterious new female pygmy, has convinced the tribe to help her on her quest to find the rest of her missing tribe mates (more pygmies!?) and save them from the maleficent Newbie! Will this be the issue that gives us even more new pygmy characters!? Who are the bubble breathing people? And where has Nooby disappeared to!? The action and mystery continue to pile up so grab your copy and join us! Don't forget that the Pocket God Comic is updated frequently with all kinds of extras including the Pygmy Peril newsletter (The Klik's Six Contest winners will be announced shortly!), an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of of the first Pocket God animated short, free Little Green Men comic short stories, and more cool stuff on the way!
name: A Quest Called Tribe Part 2 (of 4)

description: In this issue's undersea adventure...the Guys meet the Girls! Is it a 'Date with Density'? ...Or are they just SUNK! And if there are girls around, where is Nooby? He's on the receiving end of a very pointy stick, that's where!!! The group makes friends with some dwellers of the deep in their search for evil Newbie. But will their help be enough? This isn't just some fluff-story! The outcome of this arc will change things for the Pygmies for all time! (No...really. I wouldn't kid you about this.) Don't forget that the Pocket God Comic is updated frequently with all kinds of FREE extras including The Pygmy Peril newsletter, an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of the first Pocket God animated short, free Little Green Men comic short stories, and more cool stuff on the way! And The Pygmy Peril #12 is available NOW! The 'Dev-Corner' covers a very...stinky...subject! We have one last round of "Oh So Close!" entries before we announce the winners of the KLIK'S SIX Contest next issue! And the LITTLE GREEN MEN confront a toothy problem!
name: A Quest Called Tribe Part 3 (of 4)

description: Final Chapter of the 'A QUEST CALLED TRIBE' story arc! This issue... NOBODY DIES! (Well, not in the tribes at least.) It's a Pocket God FIRST! How did they do it? How did they go an entire issue without someone getting smoked? You will just have to read it to find out! The two tribes come together against evil Newbie in the conclusion of this action-packed story arc. But will the tribes choose to stay together afterwards? Friendships are forming while others are being strained to the breaking point! Don't forget that the Pocket God Comic is updated frequently with all kinds of FREE extras including The Pygmy Peril newsletter, an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of the first Pocket God animated short, free Little Green Men comic short stories, and more cool stuff on the way! And the Pygmy Peril #13 is coming SOON! Finally we will announce the winners of the KLIK'S SIX contest! Who will be recognized as one of the TOP SIX FANS? Will it be you? This issue is devoted entirely to our winners, with excerpts from stories, photos of fan-art, and MORE! Oh, and the LITTLE GREEN MEN show up also!
name: A Quest Called Tribe Part 4 (of 4)

description: Para-Abnormal Activity: A one-shot! While trying to get home from their previous adventure, the two-tribes crash into a mysterious island. With the girls currently unable to regenerate, this may not be the best time to hang out on a haunted island. HAUNTED? Yep... Ghosts, a mystery, and... MURDER! It's an ooky-spooky, extra-kooky episode of Pocket God! Don't forget that the Pcket God Comic is updated frequently with all kinds of FREE extras including The Pygmy Peril newsletter, an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of the first Pocket God animated short, free Little Green Men comic short stories, and more cool stuff on the way! And The Pygmy Peril #14 is available NOW! 'Dev-Corner' is about the origin of the species. We drop clues about the NEXT BIG CONTEST! And, of course, we have your email to answer! All that, and the LITTLE GREEN MEN too!
name: Para-Abnormal Activity Part 1 (of 1)

description: Gem Cell Research: Part 1 of 4! NEW STORY ARC! Both Tribes finally make it safely back to the girls' island! But how long the boys will stay there is a matter of contention! Some wouldn't mind if they stayed... some would like to see them go already. And with the Girl's gem broken to pieces, would they be safer if the guys stayed or left? Oh, and Nooby makes a new friend.. well, we know how that usually goes... Don't forget that the Pocket God Comic is update frequently with all kinds of FREE extras including The Pygmy Peril newsletter, an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of the first Pocket God animated short, free Little Green Men comic short stories, and more cool stuff on the way! And the Pygmy Peril #15 is available NOW! Featuring the return of FAN ART and Dev-Corner covers CAST OF PYGMIES: PART 2 as Allan recounts how the girls went from being an idea to the pygmies that stole our hearts! We announce the NEXT BIG CONTEST! And of course we have your email to answer! All that, and the LITTLE GREEN MEN TOO!
name: Gem-Cell Research Part 1 (of 4)

description: New App Design, New Comic! "Gem Cell Research: Part 2 of 4!" Sweet Jumpin' Laser-Sharks! What are Klik & Teela up to NOW? To repair the girls' gem, they need the laser. To get the laser, they have to catch the Laser-Shark! ... But is that really such a good idea? Are they going to need a bigger raft, or end up as just so much shark-bait? Nevermind that... who is Linsee cuddling up with?! And how is Nooby's new see-weed buddy doing? All these questions and more are answered in this Sharktastic Laserific issue! All that and in a SWEET NEW APP DESIGN! And don't forget that the Pocket God Comic App is updated frequently with all kinds of FREE extras such as The Pygmy Peril newsletter (which includes free Little Green Men comic short stories), and an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of the first Pocket God animated short! Speaking of... The Pygmy Peril #16 is available NOW! We have more Fan Art, 'Dev-Corner' profiles another member of the Pocket God crew: Thomas Dye, and we have a NEW feature: "Chillin' with a Villain"! We also announce the first competition in the official OLYMPYGS competition! All that, plus the usual features, letters and of course the LITTLE GREEN MEN too!
name: Gem-Cell Research Part 2 (of 4)

description: Gem Cell Research: Part 3 of 5! You’ll never guess what that Seaweed Monster is up to! ‘Trying to kill them’? Uh, yeah, so I guess you did guess. But can the tribes all get away from it or not? That’s the question! The girls’ regeneration gem is still busted, so no more second chances for them! This drives Sun and Ooga to train both tribes in what to do in an emergency…cause you KNOW there is going to be another one of those sooner or later! Meanwhile, Klik and Teela work to fix the girls’ gem. And it’s looking pretty good too! But can they fix the broken gem before someone dies of a broken heart? This issue PROMISES you the most shocking and unexpected ending of any issue so far! And if you are shocked and amazed by that, just wait until you see what we have in mind for parts 4 & 5! And don't forget that the Pocket God Comic is updated frequently with all kinds of FREE extras such as The Pygmy Peril newsletter (which includes free Little Green Men comic short stories), and an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of the first Pocket God animated short! Speaking of… The Pygmy Peril #21 is available NOW! It has Thomas Dye’s Post-Comic-Con Report, more Fan Art, Fan Mail, and not only do we announce another winner in our own official Olympygs, we also announce the amazingly amazing LAST competition in the official OLYMPYGS competition! It’s huge! It’s the TRIATHLON OF TERROR! All that, plus the usual letter from the Editor, and of course the LITTLE GREEN MEN too! And it’s still FREE!
name: Gem-Cell Research Part 3 (of 5)

description: Gem Cell Research: Part 4 of 5! Creeping clamshells! Teela can’t really be dead, right? I mean…it’s Pocket God! No one really dies…do they? Well, maybe it’s not too late to do something about it! Can Klik get the girls’ Gem working in time to pull Teela back? Or is she pushing up daisies for real-like? And what about that weird Seaweed Monster from last issue? Now that the tribes have had some training, are they ready to tackle him again? They better be, because he shows back up again this issue! Shock follows shock as “Gem Cell Research” keeps developing! And don't forget that the Pocket God Comic is updated frequently with all kinds of FREE extras such as The Pygmy Peril newsletter (which includes free Little Green Men comic short stories), and an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of the first Pocket God animated short! Speaking of The Pygmy Peril… Issue #22 is available NOW! And it’s fat-packed with awesome coolness! It has part 1 of Thomas Dye’s ‘Music of Pocket God’ article, we announce prizes and another winner in our own official Olympygs contest. All that, plus more Fan Art, Fan Mail, and the usual letter from the Editor, and of course the LITTLE GREEN MEN too! And Pygmy Peril #23 will be out shortly!
name: Gem-Cell Research Part 4 (of 5)

description: Gem Cell Research: Part 5 of 5! Wow! Huge action-issue this time! We may need a head-count at the end of the story to see who is still with us! There are answers to questions in this issue, like what IS that seaweed creature anyway... But when the answers are uncovered, more questions pop up, like as what IS that seaweed creature anyway??? Also, what happened with the Girls’ gem? Whereas it’s the relationships that help bind these two tribes together, it’s the relationships that might also pull them apart! You just have to check out the story as Gem Cell Research comes to its crashing conclusion! And don't forget that the Pocket God Comic is updated frequently with all kinds of FREE extras such as The Pygmy Peril newsletter (which includes free Little Green Men comic short stories), and an EXCLUSIVE re-mastered version of the first Pocket God animated short! Speaking of The Pygmy Peril… Issue #24 is available NOW! Now with 20% more Fish jokes! This issue has part 3 of Thomas Dye’s ‘Music of Pocket God’ article, cool stuff from fans (like you) in Pretty Pygtures, the usual insane letters from fans (like you) in the Outhouse Input, and we announce the winners of ‘Klak’s Hungry, Hungry Fishes’ from our Olympygs contest! And of course we have the usual letter from the Editor, and the LITTLE GREEN MEN too! All that and The Pygmy Peril is still free! FREE, I tell you!
name: Gem-Cell Research Part 5 (of 5)

description:
2009's Prison Pit was an unadulterated smash hit upon its release at the 2009 Comic-Con International, and the balls-to-the-wall series returns with more action and mayhem like only Johnny Ryan can deliver — again starring CF, the shirtless outer space barbarian antihero who remains damned to the Prison Pit (a vast wasteland beneath the crust of a barren planet, populated by the worst of the worst, where violence is the only law and evil creatures roam free). In this second volume, CF tries to get revenge against the evil behemoth that took his arm, and then winds up playing an unwilling participant in an elaborate escape attempt from the Pit.

Prison Pit blends Ryan’s fascination with WWE wrestling, grindhouse cinema, first person action video games, Gary Panter’s “Jimbo” comics, and Kentaro Miura’s “Berserk” Manga into a brutal and often hilarious showcase of violence like no other comic book ever created.
